# Inventory Optimization Analysis

## Problem Context  
Retail stores face inefficient inventory management, causing financial and operational losses.

## Stakeholders  
- Decision-maker: Store manager  
- Users: Inventory staff  

## Objectives  
Develop predictive models to:  
1. Optimize stock levels  
2. Reduce overstock/stockouts  

## Success Metrics  
- Prediction error rate < 15%  
- 20% higher inventory turnover  
- User satisfaction â‰¥4/5  

## Data Sources  
- 2 years of sales records  
- Current inventory data  
